<table>
  <tr>
    <td>
      <label for="xythos_url">Xythos URL</label>
    </td>
    <td>
      <input id="xythos_url" name="config[xythos_url]" value="<%= @wiki.config[:xythos_url] %>" size="50" type="text" />
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>&nbsp;</td>
    <td>
      <p>This is the URL of the Xythos server.
    Examples include:</p>
      <code>
        <pre>http://xythos.mydomain.com</pre>
      </code>

      <code>
        <pre>http://xythos.mydomain.com:8080</pre>
      </code>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>
      <label for="xythos_authentication">Authentication Path</label>
    </td>
    <td>
      <input id="xythos_authentication" name="config[xythos_authentication]" value="<%= @wiki.config[:xythos_authentication] %>" size="50" type="text" />
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>&nbsp;</td>
    <td>
      <p>This is the path of the authorization directory. To check if the user is authorized, a file will be created in this directory. 
    So this directory should only allow writes by the owner. In the path, add #{login} where the user's login should be placed.
    Examples include:</p>Internal Xythos user-model example:
      <code>
        <pre>/Users/#{login}</pre>
      </code>LDAP user-model example:
      <code>
        <pre>/Users/#{login}@ldap.com</pre>
      </code>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>
      <label for="xythos_principal">Principal Path</label>
    </td>
    <td>
      <input id="xythos_principal" name="config[xythos_principal]" value="<%= @wiki.config[:xythos_principal] %>" size="50" type="text" />
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>&nbsp;</td>
    <td>
      <p>This is the principal path which is used to retrieve the user name. 
    In the path, add #{login} where the user's login should be placed.
    Examples include:</p>Internal Xythos user-model example:
      <code>
        <pre>/xythoswfs/principals/users/#{login}</pre>
      </code>

      <code>
        <pre>/xythoswfs/principals/ldap/ldap.com/#{login}</pre>
      </code>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>
      <label for="xythos_default_role">Default Role</label>
    </td>
    <td>
      <select id="xythos_default_role" name="config[xythos_default_role]"><%= options_for_select(WikiConfig.roles, @wiki.config[:xythos_default_role]) %></select>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <td>&nbsp;</td>
  <td>
    <p>This is the role which users will initially be assigned. 
    Usually this will be 'Editor', but it could also be 'User' in order
    to have a chance to verify the user and then manually change the role.</p>
  </td>
</table>
